The paper presents a query engine for running ad-hoc, interactive SQL queries on large volumes of data, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The engine uses sampling-based techniques to achieve bounded response times and bounded errors, which involves data structures and algorithms for sampling and approximation (cs.DS, cs.DC). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for maintaining and selecting samples, which is related to optimization and machine learning (cs.DM). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on a real-world workload, which involves empirical evaluation and statistical analysis (cs.LG).
